http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Two-centres-inaugurated-at-NMIT/article14009940.ece

The ‘Centre for Systems Innovation’ and ‘Centre for Global studies’ were inaugurated at Nitte Meenakshi Institute of Technology (NMIT). The Nitte School of Management and NMIT also signed a MoU with the North Dakota State University (NDSU) to further research and development, faculty and student exchange programs. “Higher education institutions must start centres for multi-disciplinary research to make the best use of the opportunities given by the innovation driven global economy,” said Dean M. Bresciani, president, NDSU.